{
  "text": "A similar transition has shown to cover the entire W -band in simulations only, with S 11 < \u221215 dB; S 21 > \u22120.55 dB, for r = 2.2 [CITATION_1] . Still, a bondwire or flip-chip design is needed to interface a high-permittivity MMIC to the low permittivity application board featuring the transition. The E-plane probe design in [CITATION_2] covers the entire W -band, but also employs a low-permittivity substrate ( r = 2.2) and requires cutting of the substrate, which is undesired in the case of direct MMIC transitions. The 90\u00b0radial probe in [CITATION_3] has a 45% fractional-Bandwidth, but it needs a \u03bb/4 back-short and is an E-plane split-block solution. The H -plane split block Substrate Integrated Waveguide (SIW)-to-WG direct transition in [CITATION_4] ( r = 3) exhibits an S 11 < \u221215 dB;",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "44699445",
    "19103132",
    "1026243",
